============ MODES ============ 
===============================

*) NORMAL MODE
H                          Top screen
M                          Middle screen
L                          bottom screen
w/W
e/E
b/B
0                          Start of line
gg                         Start of file
G                          End of file
g_                         Last non-blank character of the line
f{char}                    jump to next occurrence of {char} => ; | ,
t{char}                    jump to before occurrence of {char}
T{char}                    jump to prev occurrence of {char}
zz                         Center cursor on screen
<C-f>                      Move forward one fullscreen
<C-b>                      Move back one fullscreen
<C-d>                      Move forward 1/2 screen
<C-u>                      Move back 1/2 a screen
a/A
i/I
o/O
ea                         Insert (append) at the end of the word
gea                        Insert (append) at the end of pre word
cc                         Change entire line
r                          Replace a single character
cw                         Change start of next word
ciw                        Change current word
u                          undO
<C-r>                      Redo
>>                         Indentation right
<<                         Indentation left
t                          Tag
i                          inside
a                          Around
*                          Jumps forward next match current world
<C-z>                      Exit vim => "fg" to open again
%                          Jump between opening and closing sets of parentheses [] {} ()
m[a-zA-Z] => `[a-zA-A]     Sets a mark then jumps to mark

*) INSERT MODE
A                          Normal => Insert: Edit last line
S                          Normal => Insert: Edit current character
ciw                        Normal => Insert: Edit curretn word
<C-r>0                     Paste the yanked text
<C-w>                      Remove backward word
<C-e>                      Remove forward word
<C-a>                      Remove word
<C-c>                      Insert mode => Normal mode
<C-d>                      Indentation
<C-t>                      undo-indent
<C-v>                      Duplicate line
<C-u>                      Remove current cursor to begin
<C-b>                      Remove current cursor to end
<C-h,j,k,l>                Move cursor
<C-p,n>                    Suggestion

*) VISUAL MODE
v                          Character-wise
V                          Line-wise
<C-v>                      block-wise
gv                         Reselect the last visual mode

*) COMMAND-LINE MODE
:[range]m {address}        Move lines
:[range]t {address}        Copy lines
:[range]d [x]              Delete range [into register x]
:[range]y [x]              Yank range [into register x]
:[range]s/{from}/{to}/[g|c] Replace 
:[line]p [x]               Put the text from register x to line
:[range]normal {commands}  Execute Normal mode {commands} to below
<C-d>                      List possible completions
:!                         Run terminal command
<C-[>                      Command-line => Normal mode

============ FILES ============ 
===============================

*) Buffer
:ls                        List buffer
[b                         Prev buffer
]b                         Next buffer
[B                         First buffer
]B                         Last buffer
:db[elete] N1 N2 N3        Delete buffer number N1, N2, N3
:N,M bd

*) WINDOWS
<C-w>s
<C-w>v
:sp[lit] {file}
:vsp[lit] {file}
<C-w>w                     Cycle
<C-w>h                     Left
<C-w>j                     Below
<C-w>k                     Above
<C-w>l                     Right
:clo[se] = <C-w>c          Close the active window
:on[ly] = <C-w>o           Keep only the active window
<C-w>=
<C-w>_                     Maximize Height
<C-w>|                     Maximuze Width

*) TABS
<C-w>T                     Move current window into its own tab
:tabc                      Close the current tab page
:tabo[nly]                 Keep the active tab page, closing all others
:{N}gt                     Switch to tab page number {N}
:gt                        Next page
:gT                        Pre page

*) SEARCH FILES
,hh                        History files
,h:                        History command vim
,h/                        History terminal
<C-q>                      Close FZF
<C-p>                      Search files
<C-p>p                     Search Git files
,f                         Search matching content files + files path
,g                         Search commits
,b                         Search buffers

*) FILES MANAGEMENT
,n                         Open files management
o                          Open prev window
go                         preview window
T                          Open new tab silently
i                          Open split
gi                         Preview split
s                          Open vsplit
gs                         Preview vsplit
C                          Change tree root to selected dir
u                          Move tree root up a dir
p                          Go to parent
P                          Go to root
K                          Go to first child
J                          Go to last child
I                          Hidden files

============ GETTING AROUND FASTER ============ 
===============================


============ REGISTERS ============ 
===============================
"                          Unnamed reigster
0                          Yank register (y)
a-z                        Named register
_                          Black hole register is a place from which nothing returns
+ | *                      Clipboard | Selection registers
=                          Expression register
"{register}{commands}      Do commands with register
:reg "{register}           Inspect the contents of register
<C-r>{register}            Do register on insert mode

============ PATTERNS ============ 
===============================

============ TOOLS ============ 
===============================

*) GIT
:G                         Git Command
git config --global credential.helper cache
:GWrite                    git add 
:Gdiffsplit                git diff
:Gvdiffsplit
:GDelete                   git rm

*) VIM-SURROUND
cs{char1}{char2}           Change surround {char1} pairs to {char2} pairs
cst{char}                  Change surround tag to {char}
ds{char}                   Delete surround {char} pairs
S{char}                    Add surround {char} on visual mode
ys{command}{char}          Add surround {char} on normal mode: yss)

*) COMMENTARY
gcc                        Comment line
gcap                       Comment paragraph
:7,10Commentary            Comment range lines
visual mode + gc           Comment by visual mode

